commit.message:
Added Kerberos auth and support protocol 5 and 6 (#7)

* initial playing with kerb auth

* some more playing around

* Tidied up GSSAPI code and updated tests to use pytest and newer standards

* Removed Python 2.6 from appveyor

* Added SPNEGO auth and newer CredSSP protocol versions

* removed powershell stop behaviour to get build working

* removed explicit server version check as it differs across builds

* Changed auth backend to favour other libraries instead of implementing SPNEGO ourselves

* Added pywin32 to Windows dependencies, fixed up NTLM GSSAPI auth

* Changed pywin32 to pypiwin32

* Moved pywin32 to optional dependency

* Added pywin32 to some appveyor builds that would work with it

* Updated README and added specific SSPI test

* Added check for gss-ntlmssp when checking if ntlm is available

commit.message:
Message encryption (#5)

* added support for message encryption

* added quiet option for functional tests

* Added coverage to appveyor so we can view it in the logs

* fix typo in README and updated wrap and unwrap loop

* Added loggers for debugging

* Fix for Python 3

* Added logic to calculate the trailer size for message encryption
changing version for new release (#4)

Add support for older pyOpenSSL (e.g. RHEL6) (#3)

This is a small fix to ensure that older pyOpenSSL versions (e.g. version 0.13.1 on RHEL6) are supported out-of-the-box.
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master'
Added README badges

Feature/ci tests (#1)

Added CI testing

* Rework of the asn scripts to use more generic functions that are shared by all
* Renamed main class from CredSSPAuth to HttpCredSSPAuth to keep in line with other requests packages
* Added support for local account (it suprisingly works)
